    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a masterfully preserved 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), representing the final and most refined iteration of the chassis. This example is powered by a 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine featuring VarioCam Plus for an optimized torque curve across the RPM range. The drivetrain is anchored by a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, providing short-throw precision and mechanical tactile feedback. Critically, the IMS bearing has been proactively replaced with a ceramic dual-row upgrade, and the rear main seal remains perfectly dry. The suspension geometry is flawless, utilizing a multi-link rear setup and MacPherson struts that maintain original factory kinematics for exceptional lateral loading. With zero deferred maintenance, consistent paint meter readings, and a pristine undercarriage free of oxidation, this is a concours-level driver's car.",
